How Opencode works

Claim Issue

It doesn't matter whether you know how to solve it. Don't look out for issues you know how to solve, but rather to the once you don't know how to solve! This will be your opening door to learning something new.

Solve Issue

After claiming the issue, now it's the time to explore ways on how to proceed.
Mentors and Google will be to your rescue here. Take advantage of both to the most.

Open a Pull Request

After reading everything on internet ever written and those to be written in future, it's the time to open your pr.
This will be the golden moment, where you will discover another 100 ways git could make you cry!

Climb the Leaderboard

After spending another sleepless night to see your pr getting merged it's the time to climb up the leaderboard and enjoy that shortliving "I love Programming" feeling!

Past Projects

PhotoStore

A buggy web application to store and share your photos

Ask Us (Backend)

AskUs is a discussion forum designed for the students of IIITA to ask questions, share the experiences and to know what other peeps are up to.

GeekChat

GeekChat is a simple bi-directional communication app where users can join rooms and have live text messaging with other users present in the room.

Leaderboard Frontend

Live leaderboard for all Opencode'21 contributors.

PanoViewer

An OpenGL based Image Viewer for 360 degrees Panoramic Images.

GoGit

GoGit aims to improve the Git and GitHub skills of the contributors by completing some tasks.

Geek Editor Backend

Geek Editor Backend is the backend of the geek editor project. It provides various APIs to the client.

Lets-Design-2.0

This repository consists of tasks related to Graphic Designing including logo designing, typography, poster designing, and 3D designing.

Warriors

Warriors is a Web3 MMO Game built on Polygon. Generate your warriors and fight against the world!

Collaborative-Web

The Opencode' 21 Collaborative website!

OpenCode Revamp

A project to revamp and redesign certain sections of the OpenCode website.

Code-Trouble

A repo that gives you an oppurtunity to you to become Sherlock Holmes and debug the code like a detective in a crime movie.

Productivity-Tracker

An application to track our day to day Work Progress, with the help of interesting imagery like Graphs and charts which will motivate us be productive.

Ask-Us-Frontend

Flutter based android app somewhat like Quora, designed to ask questions, share experiences and to know other peeps are up to.

Collaborative App

The Official Android Application of OpenCode'21.

Auction-DApp

A decentralized application for bidding on Ethereum blockchain.

Geek-Editor-Frontend

An online compiler, like a codepen where you can write, compile, execute and save code all in one place.

Find-My-Roomie

A UI/UX based project where you have to find the right balance between the functionality and UI/UX of the app in order to make it a successful one.

Numismatics

Nuismatics is Java based Android Project which would help you manage all your expenses as well as earnings with graphical analysis.

Coder-Queen

A girls-only project which consists of a website and an app to display curated hot news, and tweets as per the user's interests.

Testimonials

I am grateful to Opencode for kickstarting my journey in tech and all things Development. Over the course of the Hackathon, I went from knowing very little about different technical domains to having contributed in nearly every diverse repository in the event. Opencode is not only challenging for those familiar with dev, but also an immense learning opportunity for anyone with just the right amount of zeal and persistence. I learned a myriad of things I never thought I'd do that I still use years after the Hackathon, because learning is perpetual and stays with you forever. I had the best mentors who guided me every step of the way, eventually welcoming me into the FOSS wing as my fascination with Open Source was kindled.
